    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "**Nit** [DEREM-1] The first clause is the real value: it explains a non-obvious race. The second clause (\"so find the user message rather than asserting an exact count\") restates what `slices.IndexFunc` and `userMsgIdx` already show. Trim to the trap:\n\n```go\n// The chat daemon may insert an assistant response before this runs.\n```\n\nAlso, this 5-line block (comment + IndexFunc + assertions) is duplicated verbatim in `TestSubsequentSendWithoutOverrideUsesPersistedModel`. A small helper like `findUserMessage(t, messages)` would centralize both the rationale and the logic.\n\n*(Gon, Mafu-san)*\n\n> \ud83e\udd16",
